			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Are you passionate about developing an awesome user interface that is used by millions everyday? We are looking for a creative and enthusiastic front end developer with strong coding skills and a passion for technology.</p>
<p>
We are Plentyoffish Media, the world leader in online dating with over 60 million members and growing. We&#39;re looking for a Front End Developer to take our products to the next level. Come join our team of driven and passionate professionals and become a part of a recognized and cutting-edge company!</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>So, what will you do?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Work closely with other developers, product managers and designers to build awesome, responsive user experiences for our millions of users</li>
<li>
Ensure applications are maintained with optimal performance and scalability</li>
<li>
Work within our small development team, be part of the full product cycle making decisions and building software that changes the way millions of people connect.</li>
<li>
Work in our highly collaborative environment, share your expertise, make everyone else better and facilitate constant learning.</li>
<li>
Optimize your work as it will be loaded billions of times per month.</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>What does our ideal candidate look like?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
BS Computer Science or equivalent combination of education and professional work experience</li>
<li>
5+ years of front-end development using HTML/CSS and Javascript, and a strong interest in UI design</li>
<li>
Solid understanding of .NET,&nbsp; XHTML, HTML5, W3C, knowledgeable about the various javascript and css frameworks available</li>
<li>
Capable of multi-tasking and able to manage projects</li>
<li>
Constantly curious about how to build and extend interactive UI components, screen transitions and animations</li>
<li>
Obsessive about semantic markup, separation of data/presentation and optimized media</li>
<li>
Detail-oriented and will to invest in getting everything to feel just right (e.g. &quot;not done perfecting that easing function&quot; or &quot;I just shaved 52 bytes off that transparent PNG&quot;</li>
<li>
Solid written and verbal communication skills. You&#39;re not afraid to speak up and share your ideas.</li>
<li>
Experience in the social networking, dating, or other subscription-based business is a plus.</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
